                  <interp inst="t18170702-21-crimeloc114" type="placeName" value="Pavement, in Moorfields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18170702-21-crimeloc114" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18170702-21-off112 t18170702-21-crimeloc114"></join>. At eight o'clock in the morning of the 27th of June, the veil hung at my door. My apprentice gave the alarm, and pointed the prisoner out - A man brought him back. I picked the veil off the ground-it was about two yards from him when he was taken.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18170702-21-person205">
                  THOMAS 
                  FRENCH
               <interp inst="t18170702-21-person205" type="surname" value="FRENCH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170702-21-person205" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18170702-21-person205" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am shopman to Mr. Clarke. I was in the cellar under the shop; as I was looking up, I saw two boys scuffing about under the window; I ran up and told Mr. Clarke - He ran out, the veil was gone. I am certain that the prisoner was one of them. As soon as I got into the street I saw him drop the veil.</p>
